analysis: The documents primarily concern land reservations and modifications in Alaska, often involving the transfer of land control between different government departments (e.g., Agriculture, Interior, Commerce, War Department) for specific purposes like game preservation, military use, flood control, education, radio stations, aviation fields, and lighthouses. Many orders revoke or modify previous orders to accommodate new needs or correct outdated designations. The documents reflect a period of active land management and resource allocation in Alaska by the federal government.
title: Alaskan Land Reallocations for Infrastructure and Resource Management
